WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.500
Hi, I'm Tim. I'm an artist in Los Angeles and the founder of Jovie.

00:06.500 --> 00:12.000
Check out what Jovie just found.

00:12.000 --> 00:19.500
Cosmic Gate is playing EDC this weekend. Jovie knows I have a song with them called The Deep End.

00:19.500 --> 00:28.500
It connects that to the song's trance-market history, my fan graph, my Jovie Link activity, and the fact that Prime Day is coming in June.

00:28.500 --> 00:35.500
So Jovie recommends a surprise drop for next weekend.

00:35.500 --> 00:43.500
It gives me three campaign options with revenue math: a tee, a poster, and a hoodie.

00:43.500 --> 00:49.000
I approve the tee.

00:49.000 --> 01:01.500
Now Jovie creates the campaign, updates my smart link, drafts the fan notification, selects the audience, creates content tasks, schedules the launch, and monitors performance.

01:01.500 --> 01:10.000
This is why we built Jovie as an operating system. We had to control the front data layer.

01:10.000 --> 01:17.500
Artist profiles, smart links, fan notifications, payments, and campaign data.

01:17.500 --> 01:25.500
Then we realized the same agentic tools we use to run Jovie and ship thousands of PRs could help artists actually do the work.

01:25.500 --> 01:31.000
Jovie imports the artist's catalog and creates release workflows from 15 years of music industry experience.

01:31.000 --> 01:33.000
Jovie closes the loop from signal to campaign to fan action.
